{"binary":"scryrs","commands":[{"arguments":[{"description":"Path to the repository root directory","name":"PATH","required":true,"type":"string"}],"description":"Discover and analyze knowledge hotspots in a repository. Local mode is the default and reads .scryrs/scryrs.db. Live mode materializes the same HotspotsReport artifact from GET /v1/repositories/{repository_id}/hotspots?window=cumulative and does not merge local SQLite data.","flags":[{"default":"local","description":"Source mode: local (default) or live","flag":"--mode","name":"mode","type":"string","values":["local","live"]},{"description":"Live-mode scryrs server base URL (overrides .scryrs/.env SCRYRS_REMOTE_INGEST_URL)","flag":"--server-url","name":"server-url","type":"string"},{"description":"Live-mode repository identity (overrides .scryrs/.env SCRYRS_REPOSITORY_ID)","flag":"--repository-id","name":"repository-id","type":"string"}],"liveConfigPrecedence":["1. CLI flags","2. Environment variables (SCRYRS_REMOTE_INGEST_URL, SCRYRS_REPOSITORY_ID)","3. .scryrs/.env","4. scryrs.json `remote` section"],"name":"hotspots","output":{"fields":[{"description":"Version of the hotspot report output format (independent of trace event version)","name":"schemaVersion","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Name of the executed command","name":"command","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Resolved absolute path to the repository root","name":"repositoryPath","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Local mode: absolute path to .scryrs/scryrs.db. Live mode: live:<query_url> descriptor for the cumulative server query.","name":"storePath","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Local mode: store-derived metadata. Live mode: derived from live entries (subject count, evidence-row count, sentinel store fields).","name":"runMetadata","optional":false,"type":"object"},{"description":"Local mode: export-time timestamp. Live mode: generatedAt copied from the server response.","name":"generatedAt","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Array of ranked HotspotEntry objects. Live mode preserves the response entries unchanged.","name":"entries","optional":false,"type":"array"}],"mimeType":"application/json"}},{"description":"Ingest JSONL trace events from stdin or file. Defaults to remote (live) transport, submitting a single batch to POST /v1/trace-events/batch. Identity resolves by precedence: CLI flags, then SCRYRS_REMOTE_* environment variables, then .scryrs/.env, then the scryrs.json `remote` section. When live config is unresolved, the command fails fast (exit 2) with guidance instead of silently using local mode. Use --mode local for the SQLite store (.scryrs/scryrs.db).","modes":[{"description":"Read JSONL events from stdin","flag":"--stdin","name":"stdin"},{"description":"Read JSONL events from PATH","flag":"--file","name":"file","value":"PATH"},{"default":"live","description":"Transport mode: live (default, remote ingest) or local (SQLite)","flag":"--mode","name":"mode","value":"MODE","values":["live","local"]}],"name":"record","stderr":{"description":"One JSON object per rejected non-empty line (local) or per server-rejected item (remote, with line -1 and producer_event_id as the field)","fields":[{"description":"1‑based physical line number (-1 for server-rejected items)","name":"line","optional":false,"type":"number"},{"description":"Failing field/path when available, or producer_event_id for server rejects","name":"field","optional":true,"type":"string|null"},{"description":"Human-readable rejection reason","name":"reason","optional":false,"type":"string"}],"mimeType":"application/jsonl"},"transport":{"local":{"description":"Explicit opt-in (--mode local) — persists accepted events to .scryrs/scryrs.db via the canonical EventStore.","output":{"fields":[{"description":"Name of the executed command (always \"record\")","name":"command","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Version of the output envelope format","name":"schemaVersion","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Count of accepted events","name":"accepted","optional":false,"type":"number"},{"description":"Count of rejected non-empty lines","name":"rejected","optional":false,"type":"number"}],"mimeType":"application/json"}},"remote":{"configPrecedence":["1. CLI flags","2. Environment variables (SCRYRS_REMOTE_*)","3. .scryrs/.env","4. scryrs.json `remote` section","5. Git remote origin URL (repository_id fallback only)"],"description":"Default transport (live) — resolves an ingest URL from flags, env, .scryrs/.env, or scryrs.json `remote.ingest_url`. Skips .scryrs/scryrs.db entirely. Default timeout 3000 ms.","output":{"fields":[{"description":"Name of the executed command (always \"record\")","name":"command","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Version of the output envelope format","name":"schemaVersion","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Always \"remote\" when remote mode is active","name":"transport","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Count of events the server accepted","name":"accepted","optional":false,"type":"number"},{"description":"Count of idempotent (previously seen) events — non-fatal","name":"duplicate","optional":false,"type":"number"},{"description":"Count of rejected events (local validation + server rejections)","name":"rejected","optional":false,"type":"number"},{"description":"Count of server-rejected items","name":"failed","optional":false,"type":"number"}],"mimeType":"application/json"},"requiredIdentity":["repository_id","workspace_id","agent_id"]}}},{"arguments":[{"description":"Harness whose native event is being translated","name":"harness","required":true,"type":"string","values":["claude-code","pi"]}],"description":"Translate a harness's native tool event and record it (harness integration entry point; fail-open)","failOpen":true,"modes":[{"description":"Read the harness event from stdin (default; used by Claude Code)","flag":"--stdin","name":"stdin"},{"description":"Read the harness event from PATH (used by the Pi shim)","flag":"--file","name":"file","value":"PATH"}],"name":"hook","output":{"description":"Writes nothing to stdout and always exits 0 (fail-open). Errors are appended to .scryrs/hooks/<harness>-warnings.log; the harness is never blocked.","mimeType":"none"}},{"arguments":[{"description":"Agent harness name (claude-code or pi)","flag":"--agent","name":"agent","required":true,"type":"string"}],"description":"Install the scryrs trace hook for a supported agent harness (hook only). Idempotent and config-free: it never reads or writes scryrs.json or the .scryrs/ scaffold, and cannot fail on missing ingest config. Configure trace transport separately with `scryrs setup <mode>`.","name":"init","output":{"description":"Hook-focused next-step instructions on stdout (confirms the hook was installed and directs the operator to run `scryrs setup <mode>` and reload their agent harness). Errors on stderr. Does not print a remote ingest URL or `scryrs up` guidance.","mimeType":"text/plain"}},{"arguments":[{"description":"Transport mode: local (SQLite store under .scryrs/) or live (remote ingest via scryrs.json remote)","name":"mode","required":true,"type":"string","values":["local","live"]},{"description":"Live-mode remote ingest URL (overrides .scryrs/.env SCRYRS_REMOTE_INGEST_URL; resolved from env/.scryrs/.env/scryrs.json when omitted)","flag":"--ingest-url","name":"ingest-url","type":"string"},{"description":"Live-mode workspace identity (overrides .scryrs/.env SCRYRS_WORKSPACE_ID)","flag":"--workspace-id","name":"workspace-id","type":"string"},{"description":"Optional live-mode agent identity override (autogenerated per container from the hostname when omitted; not written to committed config)","flag":"--agent-id","name":"agent-id","type":"string"},{"description":"Optional live-mode repository identity override (derived from Git remote origin when omitted; not written to committed config)","flag":"--repository-id","name":"repository-id","type":"string"},{"default":false,"description":"Live-mode opt-in: scaffold the self-hosted .scryrs/compose.yml stack plus an overrides-only .scryrs/.env (requires a docker_network) for `scryrs up`","flag":"--with-compose","name":"with-compose","type":"boolean"},{"description":"External Docker network name for the --with-compose opt-in (overrides .scryrs/.env SCRYRS_DOCKER_NETWORK); not required by core setup live","flag":"--docker-network","name":"docker-network","type":"string"},{"default":false,"description":"Disable live-setup prompts; missing live config fails fast (exit 2) instead of starting the TTY-only wizard","flag":"--no-interactive","name":"no-interactive","type":"boolean"}],"description":"Configure local or live trace transport. The only command that writes scryrs.json remote and the .scryrs/ config scaffold; independent of `init` (no hook is installed or required). `mode` is a required positional (local or live).","name":"setup","output":{"description":"Next-step instructions on stdout. Errors on stderr. setup local scaffolds .scryrs/scryrs.db + .scryrs/.gitignore (never touches scryrs.json). setup live create-or-merges the committed scryrs.json remote section (ingest_url + workspace_id required; repository_id/agent_id resolved at runtime, never committed). The compose opt-in (--with-compose) additionally scaffolds .scryrs/compose.yml + an overrides-only .scryrs/.env and writes remote.docker_network. Missing required live config starts a TTY-only wizard unless non-interactive (no TTY or --no-interactive), which fails fast.","mimeType":"text/plain"}},{"description":"Start the workspace-managed live-server Compose stack from .scryrs/compose.yml, resolving the external network from scryrs.json remote.docker_network (override via SCRYRS_DOCKER_NETWORK or .scryrs/.env)","exitCodes":{"0":"Workspace-managed compose stack started successfully","1":"Docker invocation or docker compose runtime failure","2":"Missing scaffold files, missing external network, or unexpected arguments"},"name":"up","output":{"description":"Docker compose stdout on success; deterministic scaffold and network errors on stderr.","mimeType":"text/plain"}},{"description":"Run the installation and readiness diagnostic command","exitCodes":{"0":"Success with only ok/warn findings","1":"Output write failure","2":"One or more structural error findings"},"flags":[{"default":false,"description":"Emit machine-readable JSON using the same diagnostic categories as the default human-readable output","long":"--json","name":"json","type":"boolean"}],"name":"doctor","output":{"description":"Human-readable summary by default, or JSON with binary version, command surface / feature availability, resolved mode, local store status, hook status, live server reachability when configured, and docs links when --json is used.","mimeType":"text/plain or application/json"}},{"arguments":[{"description":"Path to the repository root directory","name":"PATH","required":true,"type":"string"}],"description":"Generate reviewable knowledge proposals from hotspot and graph evidence","name":"propose","output":{"description":"Validated ProposalDocument JSON files written to .scryrs/proposals/. Count written to stdout. Errors on stderr.","mimeType":"application/json"}},{"description":"Review proposal inbox artifacts without mutating source-of-truth surfaces","name":"proposals","subcommands":[{"arguments":[{"description":"Path to the repository root directory","name":"PATH","required":true,"type":"string"}],"description":"Emit deterministic JSON rows for pending, accepted, and rejected proposal states","flags":[{"default":"all","description":"Optional proposal state filter","long":"--state","name":"state","type":"string","values":["pending","accepted","rejected","all"]}],"name":"list","output":{"fields":[{"description":"Deterministic proposal identifier","name":"proposalId","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Reviewer-facing proposal title","name":"title","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Proposal target kind","name":"targetType","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"RFC 3339 proposal creation timestamp","name":"createdAt","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Current review state: pending, accepted, or rejected","name":"state","optional":false,"type":"string"}],"mimeType":"application/json"}},{"arguments":[{"description":"Path to the repository root directory","name":"PATH","required":true,"type":"string"},{"description":"Proposal identifier to review","name":"ID","required":true,"type":"string"}],"description":"Write a deterministic accepted ProposalReviewDecision under .scryrs/accepted/","flags":[{"description":"Reviewer identity","long":"--reviewer","name":"reviewer","required":true,"type":"string"},{"description":"Non-empty review rationale","long":"--rationale","name":"rationale","required":true,"type":"string"},{"description":"Explicit RFC 3339 review timestamp","long":"--decided-at","name":"decided-at","required":true,"type":"string"}],"name":"accept","output":{"description":"Writes .scryrs/accepted/{proposalId}.json on success and preserves .scryrs/proposals/{proposalId}.json unchanged.","mimeType":"none"}},{"arguments":[{"description":"Path to the repository root directory","name":"PATH","required":true,"type":"string"},{"description":"Proposal identifier to review","name":"ID","required":true,"type":"string"}],"description":"Write a deterministic rejected ProposalReviewDecision under .scryrs/rejected/","flags":[{"description":"Reviewer identity","long":"--reviewer","name":"reviewer","required":true,"type":"string"},{"description":"Non-empty review rationale","long":"--rationale","name":"rationale","required":true,"type":"string"},{"description":"Explicit RFC 3339 review timestamp","long":"--decided-at","name":"decided-at","required":true,"type":"string"}],"name":"reject","output":{"description":"Writes .scryrs/rejected/{proposalId}.json on success and preserves .scryrs/proposals/{proposalId}.json unchanged.","mimeType":"none"}}]},{"description":"Publish accepted knowledge explicitly through adapter-backed markdown or Rspress surfaces","name":"publish","subcommands":[{"arguments":[{"description":"Path to the repository root directory","name":"PATH","required":true,"type":"string"}],"description":"Publish accepted Markdown-backed review decisions to generic Markdown output","exitCodes":{"0":"Accepted knowledge published successfully","1":"Runtime or filesystem failure","2":"Usage error or publish-input validation failure"},"flags":[{"description":"Output directory for generic Markdown files","long":"--output","name":"output","required":true,"type":"string"}],"name":"markdown","output":{"fields":[{"description":"Name of the executed command (always \"publish\")","name":"command","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Publish mode (always \"markdown\")","name":"mode","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Version of the output envelope format","name":"schemaVersion","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Count of published Markdown files","name":"count","optional":false,"type":"number"},{"description":"Deterministically ordered output file paths","name":"paths","optional":false,"type":"array"}],"mimeType":"application/json"}},{"arguments":[{"description":"Path to the repository root directory","name":"PATH","required":true,"type":"string"}],"description":"Publish accepted Markdown-backed review decisions into an Rspress docs tree","exitCodes":{"0":"Accepted knowledge published successfully","1":"Runtime or filesystem failure","2":"Usage error or publish-input validation failure"},"flags":[{"description":"Rspress docs root containing _nav.json and accepted-knowledge/","long":"--docs-root","name":"docs-root","required":true,"type":"string"}],"name":"rspress","output":{"entryFields":[{"description":"Relative accepted-knowledge page path under the docs root","name":"path","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Accepted proposal identifier","name":"proposalId","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Accepted target type slug","name":"targetType","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Navigation label inserted into _nav.json","name":"navText","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Navigation link inserted into _nav.json","name":"navLink","optional":false,"type":"string"}],"fields":[{"description":"Name of the executed command (always \"publish\")","name":"command","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Publish mode (always \"rspress\")","name":"mode","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Version of the output envelope format","name":"schemaVersion","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Count of published Rspress pages","name":"count","optional":false,"type":"number"},{"description":"Deterministically ordered published entry metadata","name":"entries","optional":false,"type":"array"}],"mimeType":"application/json"}}]},{"description":"Start dashboard server and open the browser dashboard. Live is the default source mode (proxies a scryrs server); use --mode local to read local .scryrs artifacts. Live targets resolve from flags, then env, then .scryrs/.env, then scryrs.json `remote`; unresolved live config fails fast (exit 2) with guidance.","flags":[{"default":"live","description":"Source mode: live (default) or local","long":"--mode","name":"mode","type":"string","values":["live","local"]},{"default":8080,"description":"TCP port to bind","long":"--port","name":"port","short":"-p","type":"number"},{"default":"127.0.0.1","description":"Bind address","long":"--bind","name":"bind","short":"-b","type":"string"},{"description":"Live-mode scryrs server base URL (overrides .scryrs/.env SCRYRS_REMOTE_INGEST_URL)","long":"--server-url","name":"server-url","type":"string"},{"description":"Live-mode repository identity (overrides .scryrs/.env SCRYRS_REPOSITORY_ID)","long":"--repository-id","name":"repository-id","type":"string"},{"default":false,"description":"Do not open browser automatically","long":"--no-open","name":"no-open","type":"boolean"},{"default":false,"description":"Serve from filesystem instead of embedded assets","long":"--dev","name":"dev","type":"boolean"}],"name":"dashboard","output":{"description":"Vue.js SPA served over HTTP. REST API at GET /api/meta, GET /api/hotspots, GET /api/signals (live mode only), GET /api/sessions (local mode only), GET /api/sessions/:sessionId (local mode only), GET /api/events (local mode only).","mimeType":"text/html"}},{"description":"Start the central trace ingest server with live hotspot query and signal streaming endpoints","endpoints":[{"description":"Ingest trace event batches with idempotent first-writer-wins semantics","method":"POST","path":"/v1/trace-events/batch"},{"description":"Query live hotspot rankings from server-owned state; supports ?window=cumulative and optional ?session_id","method":"GET","path":"/v1/repositories/{repository_id}/hotspots"},{"description":"Server-Sent Events stream of HotspotSignal records; supports ?after=<signal_id> cursor replay/resume","method":"GET","path":"/v1/repositories/{repository_id}/signals"}],"flags":[{"default":8081,"description":"TCP port to bind","long":"--port","name":"port","short":"-p","type":"number"},{"default":"127.0.0.1","description":"Bind address","long":"--bind","name":"bind","short":"-b","type":"string"},{"default":".scryrs/server.db","description":"Server-owned SQLite store path","long":"--store","name":"store","type":"string"}],"name":"server","output":{"description":"BatchIngestResponse returned by POST /v1/trace-events/batch. LiveHotspotsResponse returned by GET .../hotspots. text/event-stream returned by GET .../signals.","mimeType":"application/json"}},{"arguments":[{"description":"Path to the repository root directory","name":"PATH","required":true,"type":"string"}],"description":"Build a repository knowledge graph from hotspot evidence and docs structure","name":"graph","output":{"description":"Single-line KnowledgeGraphDocument JSON written to stdout. Also persisted to .scryrs/graph.json.","mimeType":"application/json"}},{"arguments":[{"description":"Path to the repository root directory","name":"PATH","required":true,"type":"string"}],"description":"Generate the route manifest from a knowledge graph artifact, or query the manifest for matching entries","name":"route","output":{"description":"Single-line RouteManifestDocument JSON written to stdout. Also persisted to .scryrs/routes.json.","mimeType":"application/json"},"routeHintOutput":{"description":"Deterministic RouteHintDocument projection derived from the route manifest. Each route entry produces one RouteHintItem with identity, target, label, 1-based ordinal rank, evidence citations, and a template-derived reason. Rank is a deterministic ordinal derived from manifest entry sort order; relevance is deferred (None). Use `scryrs route explain <PATH> --query <TEXT>` to filter and rank hints by query match.","example":{"hints":[{"evidence":[{"rowIds":[1,2],"sourceKind":"local_trace_row","subject":"src/main.rs"}],"label":"src/main.rs","rank":1,"reason":"Route 'src/main.rs' (file:src/main.rs): 2 evidence link(s), subject kind file","routeId":"file:src/main.rs","target":"file:src/main.rs"}],"schemaVersion":"1.0.0"},"fields":[{"description":"Route hint schema version (always HINT_SCHEMA_VERSION = 1.0.0)","name":"schemaVersion","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Deterministically ordered array of RouteHintItem objects","name":"hints","optional":false,"type":"array"}],"hintItemFields":[{"description":"Source route entry id","name":"routeId","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Normalized load target","name":"target","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Human-readable label","name":"label","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"1-based ordinal rank from manifest entry sort order (deterministic ordinal, not final ranking)","name":"rank","optional":false,"type":"number"},{"description":"Optional relevance score — deferred for future enhancement (always null in current version)","name":"relevance","optional":true,"type":"number|null"},{"description":"Deterministic template reason citing route entry identity and evidence count","name":"reason","optional":false,"type":"string"},{"description":"Evidence provenance links copied from source route entry","name":"evidence","optional":true,"type":"array"}],"mimeType":"application/json","rankingPolicy":"Rank is a deterministic 1-based ordinal derived from manifest entry sort order (by id ascending). Relevance is deferred (None) and does not represent a frozen long-term ranking formula. Both fields are explicitly documented as deferred or ordinal."},"subcommands":[{"arguments":[{"description":"Path to the repository root directory","name":"PATH","required":true,"type":"string"},{"description":"Query text for case-insensitive substring matching against label, subject, id, target, kind, and evidence_links[].subject","flag":"--query","name":"query","required":true,"type":"string"}],"description":"Query the route manifest for matching entries using case-insensitive substring matching","exitCodes":{"0":"Success (including zero-match results)","1":"Serialization or stdout write failure","2":"Usage error, missing .scryrs/routes.json, malformed JSON, or schema version mismatch"},"matching":{"algorithm":"case-insensitive substring match","fields":["label","subject","id","target","kind","evidence_links[].subject"],"tieBreak":"Manifest entry order (by id ascending) within each tier","tiers":[{"description":"Exact string match","tier":3},{"description":"Prefix match","tier":2},{"description":"Substring match","tier":1}]},"name":"explain","output":{"description":"Single-line RouteHintDocument JSON with schemaVersion and hints array. The reason field appends '; query match on <fields>' suffix. Zero matches produces a valid document with empty hints array.","mimeType":"application/json"}}]}],"exitCodes":{"0":"Success (hotspots: JSON written, including empty entries; record local: all events accepted; record remote: no rejections or failures; init: hook installed; up: workspace-managed compose stack started; doctor: only ok/warn findings; propose/proposals: artifacts written or listed successfully; publish: accepted knowledge published successfully; dashboard: server shut down cleanly; server: server shut down cleanly; hook: always — fail-open, never blocks the harness)","1":"Hotspots: storage error. Record: one or more events rejected (local or server), or I/O error writing output. Init: I/O error. Up: docker invocation failure. Doctor: output write failure. Proposals: serialization or filesystem write failure. Publish: runtime or filesystem failure. Dashboard: port in use or artifact read error. Server: port in use or store error.","2":"Usage error; hotspots: missing/unsupported store; record: also fatal I/O error (unreadable file, store failure, missing remote identity, transport timeout, connection failure, non-2xx response, malformed response); init: unsupported harness, collision, or self-install refusal; setup: unknown/missing mode, source-checkout refusal (live), or missing/invalid/conflicting live configuration; up: missing scaffold files, missing external network, or unexpected arguments; doctor: one or more structural error findings; proposals: invalid filter, invalid proposal/review document, unknown proposal ID, or conflicting terminal review state; publish: usage error or publish-input validation failure; dashboard: invalid flags or partial live-mode configuration; server: invalid flags or bind failure."},"globalFlags":[{"action":"help","description":"Print help message and exit","long":"--help","name":"help","short":"-h"},{"action":"version","description":"Print version and exit","long":"--version","name":"version","short":"-V"},{"action":"helpJson","description":"Print machine-readable CLI surface description and exit","long":"--help-json","name":"help-json","short":"-hj"}],"rootBehavior":{"action":"help","exitCode":0},"surfaceVersion":"0.15.0"}
